Position Description
Senior Account ManagerPosition OverviewReporting to the Director of Global Partner Group (GPG), the candidate will have full ownership and revenue responsibility for a significant portfolio of Global and Key hotel chains. The main tasks of the Senior Account Manager are to drive revenue targets, rate & inventory access and contract renewals. The role requires the implementation of growth strategies for the assigned accounts as well as owning and driving GPG initiatives across the organization. Responsibilities•25% Account Management•Focus on hitting major KPIs in the short term (Rate and inventory access / Revenue growth).•Identify opportunities to help partners increase revenue and shift share.•Promote merchandising and advertising opportunities.•Provide Business Review to the leadership of the different accounts.• 25% Relationship Management••Day-to-day internal and external relationship management.•Establish relationships with suppliers by visiting partners in region regularly (once a month) and having daily phone calls.•Develop strong relationship with major internal departments to promote GPG and identify opportunities.•20% Contracting•Negotiate, understand and implement creative and complex deals.•Design deal models.•Initiate annual contract renewals for accounts.•Oversee coordination of contracts between Market Management and Suppliers.•20% Coaching & Developing Employees•Play an active role in coaching employees•10% Administrative•Provide weekly, monthly, and quarterly reporting, as required. Skills and Experience Required•A minimum of 5 years' demonstrated track record negotiating and / or account managing at a senior level.•Proven negotiation skills.•Outstanding analytical and strategic thinking skills, including demonstrated general problem-solving skills and an intense curiosity to identify emerging business trends and ensuing needs.•Excellent customer service and relationship-building ethic, strong social intelligence.•Ability to lead a presentation or workshop in front of a small to medium-sized audience.•Cross-functional experience (Market Management, Connectivity, Media Solutions, POS)•Ability to work autonomously and manage a wide variety of projects simultaneously and under deadline.•Ability to develop creative and innovative solutions.•Ability to communicate clearly and concisely, both orally and in writing.•Excellent quality control ability and strong organizational skills.•Energetic, highly motivated with a can-do attitude.•High proficiency in MS Office tools (i.e. Word, Excel, Powerpoint).•Knowledge of hospitality industry is desirable.•University degree required, preferably combined with MBA degree.Critical Competencies•Sales & Negotiation: Effectively identifies opportunities of growth, and negotiates successfully in a constructive, consultative, and collaborative manner.•Drive for Results: Drives high standards for individual, team, and organizational accomplishment; tenaciously works to meet or exceed challenging goals; derives satisfaction from goal achievement and continuous improvement.•Creativity: Comes with ideas and solutions to make the team win.*LI-LC1
